  {
    "id": "light-studies",
    "title": "Safe out there",
    "description": "Exploring the interplay of light and shadow in various environments, this series focuses on how illumination shapes our perception of space and form. Using medium format film to capture subtle tonal gradations, these photographs examine both natural and artificial light sources.\n\nThe square format of these images creates a formal framework for studying how light reveals texture, creates depth, and establishes mood. From harsh directional sunlight to soft diffused illumination, each photograph isolates a particular lighting condition.\n\nThrough this work, I investigate light as both subject and medium, demonstrating how the quality of illumination fundamentally transforms what we see and how we feel about what we're seeing. These studies serve as visual research into the foundational element of photography itself.",
